data.text:
Monday, May 10, 1993 Page: 6B QUICK WORDS: SMITH

Willard Smith

May 7, 1993

Willard Smith, 68, of Marlboro, N.J., died Friday at Centra cq State

Medical

Center, Freehold, N.JBorn in Newport Center, he was the son of the late

Harvey Ross and Martha Vellas Smith.

He worked for General Motors, Linden, N.J., for more than 32 years,

retiring in 1987.

He was an Army veteran of World War II. He was a member of American Legion

Post 350 and Veterans of Foreign Wars Post 290, both in Nanticoke.

Surviving are his wife, the former Ruth M. VanFossen; daughter, Judith

Carratello, Marlboro; two granddaughters; nephews and cousins.

Funeral services will be 10 a.m. Tuesday from the Homedel Funeral Home, 26

S. Homedel Road, Homedel, N.J.

Interment will be in the Homedel Cemetery.

Friends may call from 2 to 4 and 7 to 9 p.m. today.
